  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Deliver the poor and needy,.... From his adversary and oppressor, who is mightier than he, and draws him to the judgment seat; when it is not in his power to defend himself against him, and get out of his hands, unless a righteous judge will show a regard to him and his cause; and sometimes even an unjust judge, through importunity, will do this, as everyone ought, and every righteous one will: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "rid them out of the hand of the wicked; this was what the poor widow importuned the unjust judge for, and obtained, Luke 18:3. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "rid them out of the hand of the wicked; this was what the poor widow importuned the unjust judge for, and obtained, ",
